
Alert The Internets - Crowd Edition
===================================

A set of scripts for crowdsourcing the metalab video blog.

(More information to come - let me finish the thing first..)


Installing
----------

Installing encoding tools:
	# apt-get install mencoder
	# apt-get install ffmpeg

Installing youtube-upload (see http://code.google.com/p/youtube-upload/):
	# apt-get install python-gdata
	# svn co http://youtube-upload.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ /usr/local/src/youtube-upload
	# cd /usr/local/src/youtube-upload && python setup.py install

Building the ledctrl helper app:
	$ gcc -o ledctrl ledctrl.c

Allow the script to mount the media (the quick&dirty way for user "ati"):
	# vi /etc/sudoers
	ati ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL

Create mount point:
	# mkdir /mnt/ati

